{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501672","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501672"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:31:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:31:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1777"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1777","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1777"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.65,0.09,0.06,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1777"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"32711"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1777","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1777"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1777"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18221"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"278"},{"type":"tags","id":"2598"},{"type":"tags","id":"4967"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"658"},{"type":"contributions","id":"958"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7129"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8264"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8292"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43102"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"32711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/32711"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old man presents to clinic for review of sleepiness during the day. He reports difficulty remaining awake while at work, but admits that his desk job is monotonous at times. He has never fallen asleep while driving. He does not operate heavy machinery. He is an active smoker with ten pack year smoking history. His body mass index is 23. His tonsils are not enlarged. His uvula is slightly deviated to the left. A sleep study is performed and demonstrates an apnoea-hypopnoea index (AHI) of 4 [N\u0026lt;5].\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the MOST appropriate initial step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intensive exercise program","Smoking cessation","Melatonin","Uvuloplasty","Continuous positive airway pressure"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe AHI suggests no obstructive sleep apnoea-hypopnoea syndrome is present (AHI less than or equal to 5). Thus, the reason for the tiredness needs to be sought elsewhere.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, \u003Cstrong\u003Esmoking cessation\u003C/strong\u003E should be first encouraged. He has a healthy BMI, although regular exercise and healthy diet should be encouraged. QUIT and Sleep Health Foundation websites imply that the mechanism would be via nicotine withdrawal/insomnia: \u003Cem\u003E\u0022The evidence indicates that smoking is associated with increased insomnia severity and shorter sleep duration, particularly nightly smoking.\u0022\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECPAP\u003C/strong\u003E is the most efficacious therapy to treat OSA though its efficacy is limited by compliance. It is often used to treat moderate to severe OSA, but it is not indicated in this case where the patient\u0027s AHI is 4, which is within the normal range.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUvuloplasty\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated for a deviated uvula, which is not a significant anatomical abnormality that would warrant surgical intervention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMelatonin\u003C/strong\u003E is used to help regulate the sleep-wake cycle, but is not indicated in this case. There is no useful drug therapy for OSAHS.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntensive exercise programs \u003C/strong\u003Emay be helpful for improving overall health, but they are not specifically indicated for daytime sleepiness.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Obstructive sleep apnoea should always be considered in a patient presenting with sleepiness."],"references":["Sarkissian L, Kitipornchai L, Cistulli P, Mackay S. An update on the current management of adult obstructive sleep apnoea. Australian Journal of General Practice. 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18221"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1777"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18221","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/18221"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-02-18T20:06:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-02-18T20:06:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1777"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"32711"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","li